You = 64-bit RedHat
Me = 32-bit Ubuntu

You: yum install hadoop-0.20-native.x86_64
Me: sudo apt-get install hadoop-0.20-native

You: yum install liblzo-devel
Me: sudo apt-get install liblzo2-dev

You: Download Todd Lipcon' s LZO code f rom
https://github.com/toddlipcon/hadoop-lzo
Me: 
git clone https://github.com/toddlipcon/hadoop-lzo.git
cd hadoop-lzo
ant package
To install the jar into your local mvn repository
mvn install:install-file -Dfile=build/hadoop-lzo-0.4.14/hadoop-lzo-0.4.14.jar -DgroupId=com.hadoop.compression.lzo -DartifactId=hadoop-lzo -Dversion=0.4.14 -Dpackaging=jar

You: cp build/hadoop-lzo-0.4.10/lib/native/Linux-amd64-64/* \
/usr/lib/hadoop/lib/native/Linux-amd64-64/
Me: sudo cp build/hadoop-lzo-0.4.14/lib/native/Linux-i386-32/* /usr/lib/hadoop/lib/native/Linux-i386-32/

To install the jar into your local mvn repository
mvn install:install-file -Dfile=build/hadoop-lzo-0.4.14/hadoop-lzo-0.4.14.jar -DgroupId=com.hadoop.compression.lzo -DartifactId=hadoop-lzo -Dversion=0.4.14 -Dpackaging=jar